# Page scripts and Bootstrap load order

`layout.html` footer loads jQuery and `bootstrap.bundle.min.js`. Page-specific scripts included **before** `{{template "footer" .}}` run during HTML parse, **before** Bootstrap exists — `bootstrap` / `window.bootstrap` is undefined and modals silently fail.

## Required pattern

1. **`defer` on page scripts** placed before the footer (same as `nodelist.js`, `bbslist.js`, `compose-editor.js`):
   ```html
   <script src="/static/my-page.js" defer></script>
   {{template "footer" .}}
   ```
   Deferred scripts run after the document is parsed, so footer Bootstrap is available first.

2. **`boot()` guard** — do not initialize Bootstrap at module top level:
   ```javascript
   function boot() {
     if (typeof window.bootstrap === 'undefined' || !window.bootstrap.Modal) return;
     // wire listeners, charts, etc.
   }
   if (document.readyState === 'loading') {
     document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', boot);
   } else {
     boot();
   }
   ```

3. **Lazy modals** — create/show on first user action, not at load:
   ```javascript
   function getModal() {
     var el = document.getElementById('my-modal');
     if (!el || !window.bootstrap?.Modal) return null;
     return window.bootstrap.Modal.getOrCreateInstance(el);
   }
   ```

## Avoid

```javascript
// BAD — runs before footer Bootstrap
var modal = bootstrap.Modal.getOrCreateInstance(modalEl);
```

```html
<!-- BAD — synchronous load before footer -->
<script src="/static/page.js"></script>
{{template "footer" .}}
```

## Chart-only scripts

Scripts that do not use Bootstrap (e.g. Chart.js only) may still use `defer` for consistency; not required if they never touch `bootstrap`.
